725513f-a.text:
60th Street (formerly Thompson also John Street), east side, south from Metropolitan Avenue, shown at the S.E. corner a frame structure known as Reis Hotel in 1904. It was still standing in 1934. At the right background near Bleeker Street is P.S. No. 71.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

727415f-a.text:
Metropolitan Avenue (tracks thereon) at the S.W. corner of 60th Street, showing in the background facing Metropolitan Avenue. The former Montauk Brewery. In 1891 it was converted into a milk plant by Charles H. Flugge and became known as the Metropolitan Dairy Co..
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Neg. #1221
